<body>
    <div class="recipe">
        <h1>Chakri Recipe</h1>
        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup rice flour</li>
            <li>1/4 cup besan (gram flour)</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon red chili powder</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon ajwain (carom seeds)</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon cumin seeds</li>
            <li>A pinch of asafoetida (hing)</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon oil</li>
            <li>Water (as needed)</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Oil for deep frying</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a mixing bowl, combine rice flour, besan, turmeric powder, red chili powder, ajwain, cumin seeds, asafoetida, and salt.</li>
            <li>Heat 1 tablespoon of oil until it's hot and pour it over the dry mixture. Mix well to incorporate the oil evenly.</li>
            <li>Add water little by little and knead the mixture into a smooth and stiff dough. The dough should be non-sticky.</li>
            <li>Grease a chakri maker or press with oil and insert the star-shaped disc into it.</li>
            <li>Take a portion of the dough and place it inside the chakri maker.</li>
            <li>Press the chakri maker to form spiral-shaped chakris on a greased surface or parchment paper.</li>
            <li>Heat oil in a deep pan for frying.</li>
            <li>Gently lift the formed chakris and carefully place them in the hot oil. Fry on medium heat until they turn golden brown and crispy.</li>
            <li>Remove the fried chakris from the oil and drain excess oil on paper towels.</li>
            <li>Allow the chakris to cool down before storing them in an airtight container.</li>
            <li>Your crispy and savory Chakris are ready to be enjoyed as a popular Indian snack!</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Chakri is a spiral-shaped savory snack often enjoyed during festivals and special occasions.</p>
    </div>
</body>
